      <acqinfo>
        <head>Acquisition Information</head>
        <p>The material, which is part of a larger gift including
            books on Poe held by the Rare Books Department, was willed
            by Miss Greer to the Alderman Library in memory of Dr.
            James Southall Wilson, the Poe scholar with whom she
            stuided during her student days at the University of
            Virginia.</p>
      </acqinfo>
    </descgrp>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content Information</head>
      <p>The Greer-Poe collection consists of Miss Louise Greer's
         essays on Poe's life and work, her notes on biographies of Poe
         and his literary criticism, and correspondence addressed to
         her primarily from libraries in response to her requests for
         material concerning Poe, as well as postcards and photographs
         relating to Poe. Miss Greer, a Browning scholar whose
         manuscript 
         <title xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" render="italic" xlink:href="">Browning and America</title>is also
         held by this department, compiled this material for use in her
         graduate instruction at East Carolina College.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement>
      <head>Arrangement</head>
      <p>The collection is filed by subjet.</p>
    </arrangement>
